reflect on your own experience in His service. You'll likely be able to list many things that

00:54:00.139 --> 00:54:07.900
our Heavenly Father has done for you since you started to serve Him. Yes, Bible reading and meditation

00:54:07.900 --> 00:54:15.500
draw us closer to Jehovah our source of strength. And the more your confidence in Him grows,

00:54:15.500 --> 00:54:20.860
the stronger your bond with Him will become, and the stronger your faith in Him will become.

00:54:21.659 --> 00:54:27.019
Now related to what we just mentioned, a third thing that will help you when opposition comes

00:54:27.019 --> 00:54:33.500
is to reflect on how Jehovah has helped you through trials in the past. And that is exactly

00:54:33.500 --> 00:54:42.460
what David did. At Psalm 18 and verse 6, he said, in my distress, I called to Jehovah to my God,

00:54:42.460 --> 00:54:51.179
I kept crying for help. From His temple, He heard my voice and my cry for help reached His ears.

00:54:52.139 --> 00:55:00.460
So, did David recall Jehovah's help? Yes, he did. He heard my voice, David said, and my cry for help

00:55:00.460 --> 00:55:09.500
reached His ears. David not only remembered what had happened, he had faith that Jehovah heard Him.

00:55:10.300 --> 00:55:15.980
David was still putting that blessing to work because he never forgot all that Jehovah had done for

00:55:15.980 --> 00:55:25.019
Him. When you know that Jehovah has helped you, when you just know it, never forget it.

00:55:25.739 --> 00:55:32.780
We show gratitude when we remember and such experiences strengthen us to face the trials yet ahead

00:55:32.780 --> 00:55:40.940
of us. Now so far we've considered the need for faith when we are tempted and when we face opposition.

00:55:41.739 --> 00:55:49.500
Now we will again follow the same pattern with the third situation when we are afflicted with illness.

00:55:50.300 --> 00:55:57.260
What is the challenge? The challenge we face when we are seriously ill is to avoid questioning

00:55:57.260 --> 00:56:05.579
whether Jehovah will care for us. We must continue to remind ourselves that Jehovah loves us and

00:56:05.579 --> 00:56:12.940
that He will never abandon us. Remember the promise. Jehovah will sustain His loyal ones who are sick.

00:56:13.659 --> 00:56:18.219
And that promise is not just a general feeling that you get from reading His Word.

00:56:18.940 --> 00:56:27.099
That promise is a clear statement found in Psalm 41 and verse 3. We invite you to read it. Psalm 41

00:56:27.179 --> 00:56:32.940
and verse 3. But is it a promise to cure us? Notice what it says.

00:56:34.219 --> 00:56:42.059
Jehovah will sustain Him on His sick bed. During His sickness you will completely change His bed.

00:56:43.500 --> 00:56:53.659
Did Jehovah use the word cure here? No, He said sustain. Jehovah will sustain us. The cure will come

00:56:53.659 --> 00:57:01.500
later. But His promise to sustain His servants is a promise that we can trust. Here is our reason

00:57:01.500 --> 00:57:08.539
for faith in that promise. We know that Jehovah has compassion for those who are disadvantaged by

00:57:09.179 --> 00:57:15.500
poor health among other things. In verse 1 of that same Psalm we are assured that Jehovah will

00:57:15.500 --> 00:57:24.940
rescue the lowly one. Jehovah makes a similar loving expression at Isaiah 57 and verse 15. There he

00:57:24.940 --> 00:57:34.139
says, I reside in the high and lofty place but also with those crushed and lowly in spirit to revive

00:57:34.139 --> 00:57:42.460
the spirit of the lowly one and to revive the heart of those being crushed. I reside in the holy

00:57:42.460 --> 00:57:51.659
place he said, yet also with those crushed and lowly in spirit. Jehovah cares deeply for us,

00:57:51.659 --> 00:57:58.940
doesn't he? In his compassion he draws close to his faithful ones who are ill. But while we should

00:57:58.940 --> 00:58:05.739
have faith that Jehovah will sustain us and that is true, of course, whenever we face serious illness,

00:58:06.380 --> 00:58:13.019
what steps must we take to cope? Here are three things that we can do to work along with

00:58:13.019 --> 00:58:20.380
Jehovah's loving support. First, pray regularly for practical wisdom to deal with your illness.

00:58:21.340 --> 00:58:31.500
James 1 and verse 6 says, keep asking in faith not doubting at all. Earlier Jesus said, have faith

00:58:31.579 --> 00:58:38.460
and do not doubt. One sister with strong faith saw the need to do her part when she found out that

00:58:38.460 --> 00:58:45.659
she was seriously ill. She said, when I learned that I had cancer in my lung and colon,

00:58:45.659 --> 00:58:50.860
I thought that I had just received a death sentence. But after I got home from the doctor,

00:58:50.860 --> 00:58:59.019
I thought, okay, it's not what I expected, but I have to find a way to deal with this. So what did

00:58:59.019 --> 00:59:10.219
she do? She prayed and not just any prayer. She says, I never pray, make me better. I always pray,

00:59:10.219 --> 00:59:18.699
help me be strong and endure my illness. Beautiful example. That sister understands Psalm 41 and

00:59:18.699 --> 00:59:26.619
verse 3, doesn't she? If we do not recover from an illness, we have faith that the cure is coming in

00:59:26.619 --> 00:59:33.019
God's new world. In the meantime, we also have faith in Jehovah's promise that he will sustain us

00:59:33.019 --> 00:59:41.260
through any trial, any illness. He will change our bed as the verse said, meaning that Jehovah will

00:59:41.260 --> 00:59:50.539
see to it that our sick bed will not be one of hopelessness. Rather, we will endure with faith and

00:59:50.539 --> 00:59:56.539
hope. Many have found that their greatest comfort comes from heartfelt prayer and from reading

00:59:56.539 --> 01:00:03.659
such comforting passages in God's word. When we do this, Jehovah will give us strength and he

01:00:03.659 --> 01:00:09.500
will bring comforting thoughts to our mind. That brings us to the second thing that we can do

01:00:10.219 --> 01:00:17.179
to work along with Jehovah's promise and his loving support and it is this, study and meditate

01:00:17.179 --> 01:00:24.460
on Jehovah's promises in order to strengthen your conviction in the new world where you all have

01:00:24.460 --> 01:00:33.980
perfect health. That time is coming. As Isaiah 33, verse 24 foretells, no resident will say,

01:00:33.980 --> 01:00:43.340
I am sick. But we can meditate on such wonderful promises only if we take the time to read them.

01:00:43.980 --> 01:00:50.780
So take time to read a portion of God's word every day. Give close attention to the Psalms

01:00:51.340 --> 01:00:57.820
and to what Jesus did during his earthly ministry. Such accounts provide real life examples not

01:00:57.820 --> 01:01:04.940
only of coping, but also of godly compassion for those who are ill. And we also have such real

01:01:04.940 --> 01:01:11.099
life examples of compassion among us today. So the third thing that those who are afflicted with

01:01:11.099 --> 01:01:17.659
illness can do is benefit from association with fellow believers to the extent possible.

01:01:18.619 --> 01:01:23.980
We've come to appreciate this even more after living through a pandemic, isn't that true?

01:01:25.099 --> 01:01:30.460
One sister who has coped with serious illness says this, do not isolate yourself,

01:01:31.099 --> 01:01:37.820
allow friends to help you. There may be times when you feel alone, but don't isolate yourself.

01:01:38.780 --> 01:01:45.980
That's wise advice and it is scriptural advice. Always remember that the love we see among

01:01:45.980 --> 01:01:54.219
Jehovah's people is just a reflection of how he feels about us. After all, he gave us the ability

01:01:54.219 --> 01:02:01.420
to love others and his people show that God-like love for one another every day. So put your faith

01:02:02.059 --> 01:02:09.579
in Jehovah's sustaining power. Put your faith in the comfort from the Scriptures as well as

01:02:09.579 --> 01:02:17.900
the loving support of family and friends. Put your faith in Jehovah's sure promises and hold on

01:02:17.900 --> 01:02:24.699
to the assurance that life is worth living even when you are afflicted with a serious illness.

01:02:26.699 --> 01:02:32.860
In all that we have considered about Jehovah's promises, we see that faith is the essential quality

